title: Every Geth --fast restart results in sync from block 0, eventual crash also
body:
#### System information

Geth version: `geth version`
Version: 1.4.10-stable
Protocol Versions: [63 62]
Network Id: 1
Go Version: go1.5.1
OS: linux
GOPATH=
GOROOT=/usr/lib/go
#### Expected behaviour

Start sync at last block before geth restart
#### Actual behaviour

Starts sync at block 0
Eventually crashes and fails to fully sync

geth --fast
